gomodel:SYNGO_1296  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Impaired NMDAR-dependent plasticity at Sch-CA1 synapses in AIDA-1 cKO mice (Fig. 6). Altered GluN2A-mediated and GluN2B-mediated synaptic transmission and synaptic expression in AIDA-1 cKO mice (Fig. 4).\n\n6/9/2017 Pim\n- Since the AIDA-1 protein is preferentially localized in the PSD, the regulation of synaptic transmission and LTP induction is annotated by SynGO.. Experimental description: To generate forebrain-specific AIDA-1 cKO mice, we crossed AIDA-1(fl/fl) mice with previously characterized CaMKII-Cre transgenic mice (p. 8987)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" ;
        dc:date           "2017-09-06" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1296" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

